First Lady Michelle Obama will be making a series of appearances in the coming days. On January 11th, she will appear on The Tonight Show starring Jimmy Fallon. On January 6th, she will deliver her final remarks as First Lady at the 2017 School Counselor of the Year event at the White House. This event is part of her Reach Higher initiative, which aims to encourage post-secondary education for students across the country. The awardees from all 50 states are selected by the American School Counselor Association based on their innovative counseling programs, leadership skills, and contributions to student enhancement. Prior to the First Lady's remarks, there will be a panel featuring Education Secretary John B. King Jr., former Education Secretary Arne Duncan, actress Connie Britton, 2016 School Counselor of the Year Katherine Pastor, and First-Generation Baltimore Founder Verlando Brown. The event can be followed using the hashtags #SCOY17 and #ReachHigher.